The storage layer can be as simple as an array or dictionary of data that holds modelsinmemoryforyourapporascomplexasaCore DataorcustomSQL ORM solution that can be observed and queried with advanced predicates. The main responsibility of this layer is to store data for your application and play the role of the “ultimate source of truth” for the rest of your code. Exam- ples of what goes into this layer could be the following: Core Data, Realm, NSUserDefaults, KeyChain, Disk File storage, and in-memory arrays and dictionaries/sets.
